s1.chinese: 太史公讀春秋歷譜諜，至周厲王，未嘗不廢書而嘆也。
s1.english: Sima Qian read the Spring and Autumn Annals and various historical records. When he reached King Li of Zhou, he could not help but put down his book and sigh.

s2.english: He said: "Alas, Master Ji foresaw this!"

s3.english: When King Zhou used ivory chopsticks, Jizi sighed.

s4.chinese: 周道缺，詩人本之衽席，關雎作。
s4.english: The Way of Zhou declined, and poets took it as their theme in their songs. Thus the "Guan Ju" was composed.

s5.english: When benevolence and righteousness declined, the "Lu Ming" criticized it.

s6.chinese: 及至厲王，以惡聞其過，公卿懼誅而禍作，厲王遂奔于彘，亂自京師始，而共和行政焉。
s6.english: When King Li came to the throne, because he hated to hear about his faults, the nobles feared execution and disaster arose. King Li fled to Zhi, and chaos began in the capital, with the Gonghe administration taking power.

s7.chinese: 是後或力政，彊乘弱，興師不請天子。
s7.english: After this, some used force to govern, the strong oppressed the weak, and they raised armies without asking the Son of Heaven.

s8.chinese: 然挾王室之義，以討伐為會盟主，政由五伯，諸侯恣行，淫侈不軌，賊臣篡子滋起矣。
s8.english: However, they wielded the righteousness of the royal house to use conquest as a means to become lords of alliances. Government was by the Five Hegemons, the feudal lords acted wantonly, indulged in extravagance and immorality, and traitorous ministers and usurping sons multiplied.

s9.chinese: 齊、晉、秦、楚其在成周微甚，封或百里或五十里。
s9.english: Qi, Jin, Qin, and Chu were very weak during the Chengzhou period, their fiefs being only one hundred li or fifty li.

s10.chinese: 晉阻三河，齊負東海，楚介江淮，秦因雍州之固，四海迭興，更為伯主，文武所褒大封，皆威而服焉。
s10.english: Jin blocked the three rivers, Qi faced the Eastern Sea, Chu lay between the Jiang and Huai, Qin relied on the defenses of Yong province. The four seas successively rose up, taking turns to become hegemonic lords. The great enfeoffments praised by Wen and Wu were all awe-inspiring and submissive.

s11.chinese: 是以孔子明王道，干七十餘君，莫能用，故西觀周室，論史記舊聞，興於魯而次春秋，上記隱，下至哀之獲麟，約其辭文，去其煩重，以制義法，王道備，人事浹。
s11.english: Therefore Confucius clarified the king's way, petitioned more than seventy rulers, but none could employ him. So he looked west to the Zhou court, discussed the old traditions in the historical records, arose in Lu and arranged the Spring and Autumn Annals. Above he records Yin, below he reaches Ai's capture of the unicorn, condensing its wording and style, removing its tedious repetitions, to establish righteous principles. The king's way was complete, human affairs were harmonious.

s12.chinese: 七十子之徒口受其傳指，為有所刺譏褒諱挹損之文辭不可以書見也。
s12.english: The disciples of the seventy followers received the transmissions orally, for there were satirical, critical, praising, euphemistic, and diminishing words that could not be written down.

s13.chinese: 魯君子左丘明懼弟子人人異端，各安其意，失其真，故因孔子史記具論其語，成左氏春秋。
s13.english: The Lu gentleman Zuo Qiuming feared that his disciples would each establish different doctrines, each secure in their own opinions, losing the truth. So he comprehensively discussed Confucius's historical records and compiled the Zuo's Spring and Autumn Annals.

s14.chinese: 鐸椒為楚威王傳，為王不能盡觀春秋，采取成敗，卒四十章，為鐸氏微。
s14.english: Duo Jiao wrote a commentary for King Wei of Chu. Since the king could not completely study the Spring and Autumn Annals, he selected successes and failures, finally making forty chapters, becoming the Duo family's minor commentary.

s15.chinese: 趙孝成王時，其相虞卿上采春秋，下觀近勢，亦著八篇，為虞氏春秋。
s15.english: During King Xiaocheng of Zhao's time, his chancellor Yu Qing collected from the Spring and Autumn Annals above and observed recent trends below, also writing eight chapters, becoming the Yu's Spring and Autumn Annals.

s16.chinese: 呂不韋者，秦莊襄王相，亦上觀尚古，刪拾春秋，集六國時事，以為八覽、六論、十二紀，為呂氏春秋。
s16.english: Lü Buwei was chancellor to King Zhuangxiang of Qin. He also looked up to honor antiquity, collected and selected from the Spring and Autumn Annals, gathered events from the six states, making eight surveys, six discussions, twelve annals, becoming the Lü's Spring and Autumn Annals.

s17.chinese: 及如荀卿、孟子、公孫固、韓非之徒，各往往捃摭春秋之文以著書，不同勝紀。
s17.english: And like Xun Qing, Mengzi, Gongsun Gu, Han Fei and others, each gathered and selected from the Spring and Autumn Annals' texts to write books, differing greatly.

s18.english: The Han chancellor Zhang Cang calendared the five virtues, and the imperial censor Dong Zhongshu expounded the Spring and Autumn Annals' meanings, writing quite extensively on them.

s2639.english: Zheng Li Gong first year: Li Gong fled and after 17 years returned to enter.

s2647.chinese: 晉武公稱并晉，已立三十八年，不更元，因其元年。
s2647.english: Jin Wu Gong established and combined Jin; already established 38 years, did not change the yuan, continued from his first year.

s2648.english: Twentieth year: buried at Yong, first used human sacrifices to follow in death.

s2649.english: Twelfth year: attacked Deng and extinguished it.

s2655.english: Second year: the feudal lords attacked us.

s2663.chinese: 三十九武公卒，子詭諸立，為獻公。
s2663.english: Thirty-ninth year: Wu Gong died; son Gui Zhu established, as Xian Gong.

s2664.english: Qin De Gong first year: Wu Gong's younger brother.

s2679.english: Jin Xian Gong Gui Zhu, first year

s2680.chinese: 二初作伏，祠社，磔狗邑四門。
s2680.english: Second year: first made the Fu sacrifice, sacrificed to the She altar, split dogs at the four gates of the city.

s2681.english: Chu Du Ao Su, first year

s2692.chinese: 二燕、衛伐王，王奔溫，立子穨。
s2692.english: Second year: Yan and Wei attacked the king; the king fled to Wen, established Zi Yi.

s2698.english: Seventh year: took a Wei woman. Wen Gong's younger brother.

s2704.chinese: 十六伐王，王奔溫，立子穨。
s2704.english: Sixteenth year: attacked the king; the king fled to Wen, established Zi Yi.

s2717.english: Cai Mu Hou Xi, first year

s2720.english: Seventeenth year: Zheng seized our Zhong Fu.

s2724.english: Fourth year: executed Yi, entered Hui Wang.

s2735.english: Seventh year: rescued Zhou's disorder, entered the king.

s2740.chinese: 五太子母早死。惠后生叔帶。
s2740.english: Fifth year: the crown prince's mother died early. Hui Hou gave birth to Shu Dai.

s2742.chinese: 十四陳完自陳來奔，田常始此也。
s2742.english: Fourteenth year: Chen Wan came fleeing from Chen, Tian Chang began from this.

s2743.english: Fifth year: attacked the Li Rong, obtained Ji.

s2744.english: Fourth year: built the Mi altar.

s2745.english: Fifth year: younger brother Yun killed Du Ao and established himself.

s2748.english: Twenty-first year: Li Gong's son Wan fled to Qi.

s2751.english: Zheng Wen Gong Jie, first year

s2757.english: Twenty-third year: the duke went to Qi to observe the She sacrifice.

s2761.english: Chu Cheng Wang Yun, first year

s2782.english: Cao Xi Gong Yi, first year

s2791.english: Eighth year: completely killed the former Jin Hou's various sons.

s2807.english: Ninth year: began building Jiang capital city.

s2811.english: Wei Yi Gong Chi, first year

s2820.english: Tenth year: granted Qi Hou the mandate.

s2855.chinese: 十二太子申生居曲沃，重耳居蒲城，夷吾居屈。驪姬故。
s2855.english: Twelfth year: Crown Prince Shen resided at Qu Wo, Chong Er resided at Pu City, Yi Wu resided at Qu. Because of Li Ji.

s2886.english: Twenty-third year: attacked the Shan Rong, for Yan's sake.

s2901.chinese: 三十二莊公弟叔牙鴆死。慶父弒子般。季友奔陳，立湣公。
s2901.english: Thirty-second year: Zhuang Gong's younger brother Shu Ya was poisoned to death. Qing Fu assassinated Zi Ban. Ji You fled to Chen, established Min Gong.

s2917.english: Lu Min Gong Kai, first year

s2919.chinese: 十六滅魏、耿、霍。始封趙夙耿，畢萬魏，始此。
s2919.english: Sixteenth year: extinguished Wei, Geng, Huo. First enfeoffed Zhao Su at Geng, Bi Wan at Wei, began from this.

s2933.chinese: 二慶父殺湣公。季友自陳立申，為釐公。殺慶父。
s2933.english: Second year: Qing Fu killed Min Gong. Ji You from Chen established Shen as Xi Gong. Killed Qing Fu.

s2935.chinese: 十七申生將軍，君子知其廢。
s2935.english: Seventeenth year: Shen Sheng was general; the noblemen knew he would be discarded.

s2939.chinese: 翟伐我。公好鶴，士不戰，滅我國。國怨，惠公亂，滅其後，更立黔牟弟。衛戴公元年
s2939.english: Di attacked us. The duke was fond of cranes; the soldiers did not fight, extinguished our state. The state resented it; Hui Gong created disorder, extinguished his descendants, instead established Qian Mou's younger brother. Wei Dai Gong first year.

s2949.chinese: 魯釐公申元年哀姜喪自齊至。
s2949.english: Lu Xi Gong Shen first year: Ai Jiang's mourning came from Qi.

s2950.chinese: 二十七殺女弟魯莊公夫人，淫故。
s2950.english: Twenty-seventh year: killed younger sister Lu Zhuang Gong's consort, because of licentiousness.

s2952.english: Qin Mu Gong Ren Hao, first year

s2955.chinese: 衛文公燬元年戴公弟也。
s2955.english: Wei Wen Gong Hui first year: Dai Gong's younger brother.

s2966.chinese: 二十八為衛築楚丘。救戎狄伐。
s2966.english: Year 28: Built Chu Qiu for Wei. Saved from Rong Di attacks.

s2967.chinese: 十九荀息以幣假道于虞以伐虢，滅下陽。
s2967.english: Year 19: Xun Xi used currency to borrow passage through Yu to attack Guo, destroyed Xia Yang.

s2971.chinese: 二齊桓公率諸侯為我城楚丘。
s2971.english: Year 2: Qi Huan Gong led the feudal lords to build Chu Qiu for us.

s2982.chinese: 二十九與蔡姬共舟，蕩公，公怒，歸蔡姬。
s2982.english: Year 29: Together with Cai Ji in the same boat, rocked the duke; the duke was angry and returned Cai Ji.

s2989.english: Year 18: Because of the woman's matter, Qi attacked us.

s2998.chinese: 三十率諸侯伐蔡，蔡潰，遂伐楚，責包茅貢。
s2998.english: Year 30: Led the feudal lords to attack Cai; Cai collapsed, then attacked Chu and demanded tribute of bundled mugwort.

s2999.chinese: 二十一申生以驪姬讒自殺。重耳奔蒲，夷吾奔屈。
s2999.english: Year 21: Shen Sheng killed himself because of Li Ji's slander. Chong Er fled to Pu; Yi Wu fled to Qu.

s3000.english: Year 4: Welcomed the bride from Jin.

s3001.chinese: 十六齊伐我，至陘，使屈完盟。
s3001.english: Year 16: Qi attacked us, reached Xing, sent Qu Wan to make alliance.

s3015.chinese: 二十二滅虞、虢。重耳奔狄。
s3015.english: Year 22: Destroyed Yu and Guo. Chong Er fled to Di.

s3030.english: Year 32: Led the feudal lords to attack Zheng.

s3031.english: Year 23: Yi Wu fled to Liang.

s3033.chinese: 十八伐許，許君肉袒謝，楚從之。
s3033.english: Year 18: Attacked Xu; the Xu ruler bare-chested apologized; Chu followed it.

s3060.english: Year 25: Xiang Wang was established; feared Tai Shu.

s3063.english: Year 25: Attacked Di, because of Chong Er.

s3066.chinese: 三十公疾，太子茲父讓兄目夷賢，公不聽。
s3066.english: Year 30: The duke was ill; Crown Prince Zi Fu yielded to elder brother Mu Yi's worthiness; the duke did not listen.

s3077.chinese: 九齊率我伐晉亂，至高梁還。
s3077.english: Year 9: Qi led us to attack Jin's chaos, reached Gao Liang and returned.

s3078.chinese: 三十五夏，會諸侯于葵丘。天子使宰孔賜胙，命無拜。
s3078.english: Year 35: Summer, assembled the feudal lords at Kui Qiu. The Son of Heaven sent Steward Kong to grant the thigh meat, commanded no bowing.

s3079.chinese: 二十六公卒，立奚齊，里克殺之。及卓子。立夷吾。
s3079.english: Year 26: The duke died; established Xi Qi; Li Ke killed him. And Zhuo Zi. Established Yi Wu.

s3080.english: Year 9: Yi Wu sent Xi Rang to bribe and seek entry.

s3082.chinese: 三十一公薨，未葬，齊桓會葵丘。
s3082.english: Year 31: The duke died; not yet buried, Qi Huan assembled at Kui Qiu.

s3094.chinese: 三十六使隰朋立晉惠公。
s3094.english: Year 36: Sent Xi Peng to establish Jin Hui Gong.

s3095.chinese: 晉惠公夷吾元年誅里克，倍秦約。
s3095.english: 晉惠公夷吾元年誅里克, 倍秦約.

s3096.english: Year 10: Pi Zheng Zi Bao fled and came.

s3098.chinese: 宋襄公茲父元年目夷相。
s3098.english: 宋襄公茲父元年目夷相.

s3108.chinese: 三戎伐我，太叔帶召之。欲誅叔帶，叔帶奔齊。
s3108.english: Year 3: The Rong attacked us; Tai Shu Dai summoned them. Wanted to execute Shu Dai; Shu Dai fled to Qi.

s3112.english: Year 11: Saved the king and attacked the Rong; the Rong left.

s3119.chinese: 二十四有妾夢天與之蘭，生穆公蘭。
s3119.english: Year 24: Had a concubine who dreamed Heaven gave her orchids; gave birth to Mu Gong Lan.

s3126.chinese: 三十八使管仲平戎于周，欲以上卿禮，讓，受下卿。
s3126.english: Year 38: Sent Guan Zhong to pacify the Rong in Zhou; wished to use upper minister ritual, declined and received lower minister.

s3142.chinese: 三十九使仲孫請王，言叔帶，王怒。
s3142.english: Year 39: Sent Zhong Sun to request the king, spoke about Shu Dai; the king was angry.

s3143.english: Year 4: Famine; requested grain; Qin gave to us.

s3144.chinese: 十三丕豹欲無與，公不聽，輸晉粟，起雍至絳。
s3144.english: Year 13: Pi Bao wanted not to give; the duke did not listen; transported Jin grain; rose from Yong to Jiang.

s3159.english: Year 5: Qin had famine; requested grain; Jin violated the agreement.

s3173.chinese: 十五五月，日有食之。不書，史官失之。
s3173.english: Year 15: Fifth month, there was a solar eclipse. Not recorded; the historians omitted it.

s3175.english: Year 6: Qin captured Hui Gong and re-established him.

s3176.chinese: 十五以盜食善馬士得破晉。
s3176.english: Year 15: Used bandits who ate good horses to defeat Jin.

s3181.english: Cai Zhuang Hou Jia Wu, first year

s3190.chinese: 四十二王以戎寇告齊，齊徵諸侯戍周。
s3190.english: Year 42: The king reported Rong invasion to Qi; Qi summoned the feudal lords to defend Zhou.

s3191.chinese: 七重耳聞管仲死，去翟之齊。
s3191.english: Year 7: Chong Er heard Guan Zhong died; left Di and went to Qi.

s3194.chinese: 七隕五石。六鷁退飛，過我都。
s3194.english: Year 7: Five stones fell. Six phoenixes retreated flying, passed over our capital.

s3222.english: Qi Xiao Gong Zhao, first year

s3240.chinese: 十九滅梁。梁好城，不居，民罷，相驚，故亡。
s3240.english: Nineteenth year: extinguished Liang. Liang was fond of city walls, did not reside in them; the people were exhausted, startled each other, therefore perished.

s3273.chinese: 三十三執宋襄公，復歸之。
s3273.english: Thirty-third year: seized Song Xiang Gong, released him again.

s3284.english: Fourteenth year: Shu Dai returned again to Zhou.

s3286.english: Fifth year: returned the king's younger brother Dai.

s3287.english: Thirteenth year: Crown Prince Yu was hostage in Qin, fled and returned.

s3290.english: Thirteenth year: battle of Hong, Chu defeated the duke.

s3295.english: Thirty-fifth year: the duke went to Chu, Song attacked us.

s3302.english: Sixth year: attacked Song because they did not join the alliance.

s3303.english: Fourteenth year: Yu was established as Hui Gong.

s3304.chinese: 二十三迎重耳於楚，厚禮之，妻之女。重耳願歸。
s3304.english: Twenty-third year: welcomed Chong Er from Chu, treated him with great courtesy, married him to a daughter. Chong Er wished to return.

s3305.english: Thirty-fifth year: Chong Er passed through, treated him with great courtesy.

s3306.english: Fourteenth year: the duke died ill from the Hong battle.

s3307.chinese: 二十三重耳從齊過，無禮。
s3307.english: Twenty-third year: Chong Er came from Qi and passed through, was disrespectful.

s3310.chinese: 十六重耳過，無禮，僖負羈私善。
s3310.english: Sixteenth year: Chong Er passed through, was disrespectful; Xi Fu Ji privately befriended him.

s3311.chinese: 三十六重耳過，無禮，叔詹諫。
s3311.english: Thirty-sixth year: Chong Er passed through, was disrespectful; Shu Zhan admonished.

s3316.english: Sixteenth year: the king fled to Si. Si was Zheng territory.

s3319.chinese: 晉文公元年誅子圉。魏武子為魏大夫，趙衰為原大夫。咎犯曰「求霸莫如內王。」
s3319.english: 晉文 Gongfirst year誅son圉。魏武son為魏大夫，趙衰為原大夫。咎犯曰「求霸莫如內 Wang。」

s3320.english: Twenty-fourth year: used troops to assist Chong Er.

s3322.english: Song Cheng Gong Wang Chen, first year

s3332.english: Seventeenth year: Jin installed the king.

s3336.english: Twenty-fifth year: wished to bring in the king, army on the Yellow River.

s3354.english: Third year: violated Chu alliance, became close to Jin.

s3355.english: Wei Cheng Gong Zheng, first year

s3366.chinese: 十孝公薨，弟潘因衛公子開方殺孝公子，立潘。
s3366.english: Year 10: Xiao Gong died; younger brother Pan, because of Wei Gongzi Kai Fang, killed Xiao Gong's son and established Pan.

s3367.english: Year 4: Saved Song; repaid the shame of Cao and Wei.

s3369.english: Year 39: Sent Zi Yu to attack Song.

s3370.english: Year 4: Chu attacked us; we reported emergency to Jin.

s3380.english: Year 20: The king hunted at He Yang.

s3381.english: Year 28: The duke went to Jian Tu for audience.

s3382.chinese: 齊昭公潘元年會晉敗楚，朝周王。
s3382.english: Qi Zhao Gong Pan, first year. Assembled Jin defeated Chu, courted Zhou king.

s3383.chinese: 五侵曹伐衛，取五鹿，執曹伯。諸侯敗楚而朝河陽，周命賜公土地。
s3383.english: Year 5: Invaded Cao attacked Wei, took Wu Lu, seized Cao Bo. Feudal lords defeated Chu and courted He Yang; Zhou command granted duke land.

s3384.english: Year 28: Assembled Jin attacked Chu courted Zhou.

s3385.english: Year 40: Jin defeated Zi Yu at Cheng Pu.

s3386.english: Year 5: Jin saved us; Chu troops left.

s3387.chinese: 三晉伐我，取五鹿。公出奔，立公子瑕會晉朝，復歸衛。
s3387.english: Year 3: Jin attacked us, took Wu Lu. Duke fled; established Gongzi Xia assembled Jin courted, returned to Wei.

s3388.english: Year 16: Assembled Jin attacked Chu, courted Zhou king.

s3389.english: Year 14: Assembled Jin attacked Chu, courted Zhou king.

s3390.chinese: 二十一晉伐我，執公，復歸之。
s3390.english: Year 21: Jin attacked us, seized duke, returned him.

s3403.english: Year 4: Jin allied Wei with Song.

s3415.chinese: 七聽周歸衛成公。與秦圍鄭。
s3415.english: Year 7: Heard Zhou returned Wei Cheng Gong. Together with Qin surrounded Zheng.

s3416.english: Year 30: Surrounded Zheng; when spoken to, left.

s3419.english: Year 5: Zhou installed Cheng Gong, restored Wei.

s3423.chinese: 四十三秦、晉圍我，以晉故。
s3423.english: Year 43: Qin and Jin surrounded us, because of Jin.

s3448.chinese: 三十二將襲鄭，蹇叔曰不可。
s3448.english: Year 32: Was about to raid Zheng; Jian Shu said it was not possible.

s3463.chinese: 晉襄公驩元年破秦于殽。
s3463.english: 晉襄 Gong驩first year破秦于殽。

s3464.english: Year 33: Raided Zheng; Jin defeated us at Xiao.

s3471.chinese: 鄭穆公蘭元年秦襲我，弦高詐之。
s3471.english: Zheng Mu Gong Lan, first year. Qin raided us; Xian Gao deceived them.

s3477.english: Lu Wen Gong Xing, first year

s3479.english: Year 2: Attacked Wei; Wei attacked us.

s3480.chinese: 三十四敗殽將亡歸，公復其官。
s3480.english: Year 34: The Xiao defeated generals returned; the duke restored their offices.

s3481.chinese: 四十六王欲殺太子立職，太子恐，與傅潘崇殺王。王欲食熊蹯死，不聽。自立為王。
s3481.english: Year 46: The king wanted to kill the crown prince and establish Zhi; the crown prince was afraid and together with tutor Pan Chong killed the king. The king wanted to eat bear paw and die, but they did not listen. Self-established as king.

s3483.english: Year 9: Jin attacked us; we attacked Jin.

s3495.english: Year 3: Qin avenged our Xiao defeat; defeated us at Wang.

s3496.chinese: 三十五伐晉報殽，敗我于汪。
s3496.english: Year 35: Attacked Jin to avenge Xiao; defeated us at Wang.

s3497.chinese: 楚穆王商臣元年以其太子宅賜崇，為相。
s3497.english: 楚穆 Wang商臣first year以其太son宅賜崇，為相。

s3509.english: Year 3: The duke went to Jin.

s3511.chinese: 四秦伐我，取王官，我不出。
s3511.english: Year 4: Qin attacked us, took Wang City; we did not go out.

s3512.chinese: 三十六以孟明等伐晉，晉不敢出。
s3512.english: Year 36: With Meng Ming and others attacked Jin; Jin did not dare come out.

s3527.english: Year 5: Attacked Qin, surrounded Mai and Xin City.

s3528.chinese: 三十七晉伐我，圍邧、新城。
s3528.english: Year 37: Jin attacked us, surrounded Mai and Xin City.

s3531.english: Year 12: The duke went to Jin.

s3543.chinese: 六趙成子、欒貞子、霍伯、臼季皆卒。
s3543.english: Year 6: Zhao Cheng Zi, Luan Zhen Zi, Huo Bo, Jiu Ji all died.

s3559.chinese: 七公卒。趙盾為太子少，欲更立君，恐誅，遂立太子為靈公。
s3559.english: Year 7: The duke died. Zhao Dun as crown prince was young, wanted to establish different ruler, feared execution, so established crown prince as Ling Gong.

s3560.chinese: 三十九繆公薨。葬殉以人，從死者百七十人，君子譏之，故不言卒。
s3560.english: Year 39: Mu Gong died. Buried with human sacrifices; those who died with him were 170 people; the gentleman criticized it, so not said 'died'.

s3575.chinese: 晉靈公夷皋元年趙盾專政。
s3575.english: 晉靈公夷皋元年趙盾專政.

s3576.english: Qin Kang Gong Ying, first year

s3578.english: Year 17: Gong Sun Gu killed Cheng Gong.

s3589.chinese: 八王使衛來求金以葬，非禮。
s3589.english: Year 8: The king sent Wei to request gold for burial; it was not ritual.

s3591.chinese: 二秦伐我，取武城，報令孤之戰。
s3591.english: Year 2: Qin attacked us, took Wu City, avenged Ling Gu's battle.

s3594.chinese: 宋昭公杵臼元年襄公之子。
s3594.english: 宋昭公杵臼元年襄公之子.

s3607.english: Year 3: Led the feudal lords to save Zheng.

s3609.english: Year 8: Attacked Zheng because they served Jin.

s3623.chinese: 四伐秦，拔少梁。秦取我北徵。
s3623.english: Year 4: Attacked Qin, took Shao Liang. Qin took our Bei Zheng.

s3624.chinese: 四晉伐我，取少梁。我伐晉取北徵。
s3624.english: Year 4: Jin attacked us, took Shao Liang. We attacked Jin and took Bei Zheng.

s3630.english: Cao Wen Gong Shou, first year

s3637.chinese: 十一敗長翟于鹹而歸，得長翟。
s3637.english: Year 11: Defeated Chang Di at Xian and returned, obtained Chang Di.

s3642.english: Year 4: Defeated Chang Di at Chang Qiu.

s3655.chinese: 六秦取我羈馬。與秦戰河曲，秦師遁。
s3655.english: Year 6: Qin took our Ji Ma. Fought Qin at He Qu; Qin army retreated.

s3656.chinese: 六伐晉，取羈馬。怒，與我大戰河曲。
s3656.english: Year 6: Attacked Jin, took Ji Ma. Angry, fought us great battle at He Qu.

s3672.english: Year 7: Jin deceived and obtained Sui Hui.

s3684.chinese: 六頃王崩。公卿爭政，故不赴。
s3684.english: Year 6: Qing Wang died. Nobles contended for government, so did not announce.

s3685.chinese: 十四彗星入北斗，周史曰：七年，宋、齊、晉君死。
s3685.english: 十四彗星入北斗，周史曰：七年，宋、齊、晉君死。

s3686.chinese: 二十昭公卒。弟商人殺太子自立，是為懿公。
s3686.english: Year 20: Zhao Gong died. Younger brother Shang Ren killed crown prince and self-established, was Yi Gong.

s3687.chinese: 八趙盾以車八百乘納捷菑，平王室。
s3687.english: Year 8: Zhao Dun with 800 chariots installed Jie Kui, pacified the royal house.

s3689.english: Chu Zhuang Wang Lu, first year

s3692.english: Chen Ling Gong Ping Guo, first year

s3701.chinese: 十五六月辛丑，日蝕，齊伐我。
s3701.english: Year 15: Sixth month Xin Chou, solar eclipse; Qi attacked us.

s3702.english: Qi Yi Gong Shang Ren, first year

s3709.english: Year 34: Jin attacked us. Zhuang Hou died.

s3710.english: Year 6: Qi entered our outer wall.

s3718.english: Year 2: Did not obtain the people's hearts.

s3722.chinese: 九襄夫人使衛伯殺昭公。弟鮑立。
s3722.english: Year 9: Xiang Furen made Wei Bo kill Zhao Gong. Younger brother Bao established.

s3725.english: Cai Wen Hou Shen, first year

s3735.english: Year 11: Led the feudal lords to pacify Song.
